#. Tag: para
#: sidereal.docbook:12
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<firstterm>Sidereal Time</firstterm> literally means <quote>star time</"
"quote>. The time we are used to using in our everyday lives is Solar Time. "
"The fundamental unit of Solar Time is a <firstterm>Day</firstterm>: the time "
"it takes the Sun to travel 360 degrees around the sky, due to the rotation "
"of the Earth. Smaller units of Solar Time are just divisions of a Day:"
msgstr ""
"<firstterm>Zvezdni čas</firstterm> dobesedno pomeni <quote>čas zvezde</"
"quote>. Čas, ki smo ga vajeni uporabljati v vsakdanjem življenju, je sončni "
"čas. Osnovna enota sončnega časa je <firstterm>dan</firstterm>: čas, ki ga "
"Sonce potrebuje, da obkroži nebo za 360 stopinj zaradi rotacije Zemlje. "
"Manjše enote sončnega časa so le deli dneva:"

#. Tag: para
#: sidereal.docbook:20
#, no-c-format
msgid "1/24 Day = 1 Hour"
msgstr "1/24 dan = 1 ura"

#. Tag: para
#: sidereal.docbook:21
#, no-c-format
msgid "1/60 Hour = 1 Minute"
msgstr "1/60 ure = 1 minuta"

#. Tag: para
#: sidereal.docbook:22
#, no-c-format
msgid "1/60 Minute = 1 Second"
msgstr "1/60 minute = 1 sekunda"

#. Tag: para
#: sidereal.docbook:24
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"However, there is a problem with Solar Time. The Earth does not actually "
"spin around 360 degrees in one Solar Day. The Earth is in orbit around the "
"Sun, and over the course of one day, it moves about one Degree along its "
"orbit (360 degrees/365.25 Days for a full orbit = about one Degree per Day). "
"So, in 24 hours, the direction toward the Sun changes by about a Degree. "
"Therefore, the Earth has to spin 361 degrees to make the Sun look like it "
"has traveled 360 degrees around the Sky."
msgstr ""
"Vendar pa obstaja težava s sončnim časom. Zemlja se dejansko ne zavrti za "
"360 stopinj v enem sončnem dnevu. Zemlja kroži okoli Sonca in se v enem "
"dnevu premakne za približno eno stopinjo vzdolž svoje orbite (360 "
"stopinj/365,25 dni za celotno orbito = približno ena stopinja na dan). Torej "
"se v 24 urah smer proti Soncu spremeni za približno stopinjo. Zato se mora "
"Zemlja zavrteti za 361 stopinj, da je Sonce videti, kot da je potovalo 360 "
"stopinj okoli neba."

#. Tag: para
#: sidereal.docbook:32
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In astronomy, we are concerned with how long it takes the Earth to spin with "
"respect to the <quote>fixed</quote> stars, not the Sun. So, we would like a "
"timescale that removes the complication of Earth's orbit around the Sun, and "
"just focuses on how long it takes the Earth to spin 360 degrees with respect "
"to the stars. This rotational period is called a <firstterm>Sidereal Day</"
"firstterm>. On average, it is 4 minutes shorter than a Solar Day, because of "
"the extra 1 degree the Earth spins in a Solar Day. Rather than defining a "
"Sidereal Day to be 23 hours, 56 minutes, we define Sidereal Hours, Minutes "
"and Seconds that are the same fraction of a Day as their Solar counterparts. "
"Therefore, one Solar Second = 1.00278 Sidereal Seconds."
msgstr ""
"V astronomiji nas zanima, koliko časa potrebuje Zemlja, da se zavrti glede "
"na <quote>fiksne</quote> zvezde, ne glede na Sonce. Želimo torej časovno "
"lestvico, ki odpravlja zapletenost Zemljine orbite okoli Sonca in se "
"osredotoča samo na to, kako dolgo potrebuje, da se Zemlja zavrti za 360 "
"stopinj glede na zvezde. To rotacijsko obdobje se imenuje <firstterm>Zvezdni "
"dan</firstterm>. V povprečju je 4 minute krajši od Sončevega dne zaradi "
"dodatne 1 stopinje, za katero se Zemlja vrti v Sončevem dnevu. Namesto da bi "
"zvezdni dan opredelili kot 23 ur in 56 minut, definiramo zvezdne ure, minute "
"in sekunde, ki so enak delček dneva kot njihovi sončni primerki. Zato je ena "
"sončna sekunda = 1,00278 zvezdne sekunde."

#. Tag: para
#: sidereal.docbook:44
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Sidereal Time is useful for determining where the stars are at any given "
"time. Sidereal Time divides one full spin of the Earth into 24 Sidereal "
"Hours; similarly, the map of the sky is divided into 24 Hours of "
"<firstterm>Right Ascension</firstterm>. This is no coincidence; Local "
"Sidereal Time (<acronym>LST</acronym>) indicates the Right Ascension on the "
"sky that is currently crossing the <link linkend=\"ai-meridian\">Local "
"Meridian</link>. So, if a star has a Right Ascension of 05h 32m 24s, it will "
"be on your meridian at LST=05:32:24. More generally, the difference between "
"an object's <acronym>RA</acronym> and the Local Sidereal Time tells you how "
"far from the Meridian the object is. For example, the same object at "
"LST=06:32:24 (one Sidereal Hour later), will be one Hour of Right Ascension "
"west of your meridian, which is 15 degrees. This angular distance from the "
"meridian is called the object's <link linkend=\"ai-hourangle\">Hour Angle</"
"link>."
msgstr ""
"Zvezdni čas je uporaben za določanje, kje so zvezde v danem trenutku. "
"Zvezdni čas razdeli en polni vrtljaj Zemlje na 24 zvezdnih ur; podobno je "
"karta neba razdeljena na 24 ur <firstterm>rektascenzije</firstterm>. To ni "
"naključje; Lokalni zvezdni čas (<acronym>LST</acronym>) označuje "
"rektascenzijo na nebu, ki trenutno prečka <link linkend=\"ai-meridian"
"\">lokalni poldnevnik</link>. Torej, če ima zvezda rektascenzijo 05h 32m "
"24s, bo na vašem poldnevniku ob LST=05:32:24. Na splošno vam razlika med "
"<acronym>RA</acronym> objekta in lokalnim zvezdnim časom pove, kako daleč od "
"poldnevnika je objekt. Na primer, isti objekt ob LST=06:32:24 (eno zvezdno "
"uro pozneje) bo eno uro rektascenzije zahodno od vašega poldnevnika, ki je "
"15 stopinj. Ta kotna razdalja od poldnevnika se imenuje <link linkend=\"ai-"
"hourangle\">urni kot</link> objekta."

#. Tag: para
#: sidereal.docbook:61
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Local Sidereal Time is displayed by &kstars; in the <guilabel>Time Info "
"Box</guilabel>, with the label <quote>ST</quote> (you have to "
"<quote>unshade</quote> the box by double-clicking it in order to see the "
"sidereal time). Note that the changing sidereal seconds are not synchronized "
"with the changing Local Time and Universal Time seconds. In fact, if you "
"watch the clocks for a while, you will notice that the Sidereal seconds "
"really are slightly shorter than the LT and UT seconds."
msgstr ""
"Lokalni zvezdni čas prikaže &kstars; v <guilabel>Polje s podatki o času</"
"guilabel> z oznako <quote>ST</quote> (morate <quote>odsenčiti</quote> polje "
"tako, da ga dvokliknete, da vidite zvezdni čas ). Upoštevajte, da "
"spreminjajoče se stranske sekunde niso sinhronizirane s spreminjajočimi se "
"sekundami lokalnega in univerzalnega časa. Pravzaprav, če nekaj časa "
"opazujete ure, boste opazili, da so zvezdne sekunde res nekoliko krajše od "
"sekund lokalnega časa in univerzalnega časa."

#. Tag: para
#: sidereal.docbook:69
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Point to the <link linkend=\"ai-zenith\">Zenith</link> (press <keycap>Z</"
"keycap> or select the <menuchoice><guimenu>Pointing</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Zenith</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item). The Zenith is the "
"point on the sky where you are looking <quote>straight up</quote> from the "
"ground, and it is a point on your <link linkend=\"ai-meridian\">Local "
"Meridian</link>. Note the Right Ascension of the Zenith: it is exactly the "
"same as your Local Sidereal Time."
msgstr ""
"Pokažite na <link linkend=\"ai-zenith\">Zenit</link> (pritisnite <keycap>Z</"
"keycap> ali izberite element menija <menuchoice><guimenu>Kazanje na</"
"guimenu> <guimenuitem>Zenit</guimenuitem> </menuchoice>). Zenit je točka na "
"nebu, kjer s tal gledate <quote>naravnost navzgor</quote>, in je točka na "
"vašem <link linkend=\"ai-meridian\">lokalnem poldnevniku</link>. Upoštevajte "
"rektascenzijo zenita: je popolnoma enaka vašemu lokalnemu zvezdnemu času."
